Katharine Ross https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Katharine_Ross 0 Katharine Juliet Ross (born January 29, 1940) is an American film and stage actress. She had starring roles in three of the most popular films of the 1960s and 1970s: as Elaine Robinson in The Graduate (1967), for which she received a nomination for the Academy Award for Best Supporting Actress; as Etta Place in Butch Cassidy and the Sundance Kid (1969), for which she won a BAFTA Award for Best Actress; and as Joanna Eberhart in The Stepford Wives (1975). She won a Golden Globe for Voyage of the Damned (1976). Katharine_Juliet_Ross ( born January_29_,_1940 ) is an_American_film_and_stage_actress .
